FORMAT: 1A
HOST: http://localhost:5000

# Library Management API

Demo API quản lý thư viện đồng bộ với server Flask trong openapi-comparison/server.py.

# Group System

## API Info [/]

### Get API information [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
          "success": true,
          "message": "Library API is running",
          "data": {
            "name": "Library Management Demo",
            "endpoints": [
              "GET /books",
              "POST /borrow",
              "POST /return"
            ]
          }
        }

# Group Health

## Health Check [/health]

### Get service health [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
          "success": true,
          "message": "Service healthy",
          "data": {
            "status": "ok"
          }
        }

# Group Books

## Books Collection [/books{?q,available}]

### List books [GET]

+ Parameters
    + q: `clean` (optional, string) - Từ khóa tìm theo title hoặc author.
    + available: `true` (optional, boolean) - Lọc sách đang sẵn sàng cho mượn.

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
          "success": true,
          "message": "Success",
          "data": [
            {
              "id": 1,
              "title": "Clean Code",
              "author": "Robert C. Martin",
              "year": 2008,
              "available": true
            }
          ]
        }

### Create book [POST]

+ Request (application/json)

        {
          "title": "Domain-Driven Design",
          "author": "Eric Evans",
          "year": 2003
        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

        {
          "success": true,
          "message": "Book created",
          "data": {
            "id": 2,
            "title": "Domain-Driven Design",
            "author": "Eric Evans",
            "year": 2003,
            "available": true
          }
        }

## Book Detail [/books/{bookId}]

+ Parameters
    + bookId: `1` (number, required)

### Get book by id [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
          "success": true,
          "message": "Success",
          "data": {
            "id": 1,
            "title": "Clean Code",
            "author": "Robert C. Martin",
            "year": 2008,
            "available": true
          }
        }

+ Response 404 (application/json)

        {
          "success": false,
          "error": "Book not found"
        }

### Update book [PUT]

+ Request (application/json)

        {
          "title": "Clean Code 2nd Edition",
          "year": 2026
        }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
          "success": true,
          "message": "Book updated",
          "data": {
            "id": 1,
            "title": "Clean Code 2nd Edition",
            "author": "Robert C. Martin",
            "year": 2026,
            "available": true
          }
        }

### Delete book [DELETE]

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
          "success": true,
          "message": "Book deleted",
          "data": null
        }

# Group Members

## Members Collection [/members]

### List members [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
          "success": true,
          "message": "Success",
          "data": [
            {
              "id": 1,
              "name": "Nguyen An",
              "email": "an.nguyen@example.com"
            }
          ]
        }

# Group Borrow

## Borrow Book [/borrow]

### Borrow a book [POST]

+ Request (application/json)

        {
          "book_id": 1,
          "member_id": 2
        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

        {
          "success": true,
          "message": "Borrow successful",
          "data": {
            "book_id": 1,
            "member_id": 2,
            "borrowed_at": "2026-03-20T10:00:00Z",
            "returned_at": null
          }
        }

## Return Book [/return]

### Return a book [POST]

+ Request (application/json)

        {
          "book_id": 1
        }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
          "success": true,
          "message": "Return successful",
          "data": {
            "book_id": 1,
            "member_id": 2,
            "borrowed_at": "2026-03-20T10:00:00Z",
            "returned_at": "2026-03-21T10:00:00Z"
          }
        }

## Borrow Records [/borrow-records]

### List borrow records [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
          "success": true,
          "message": "Success",
          "data": [
            {
              "book_id": 1,
              "member_id": 2,
              "borrowed_at": "2026-03-20T10:00:00Z",
              "returned_at": "2026-03-21T10:00:00Z"
            }
          ]
        }
